---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import CtaBand from '../components/CtaBand.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Connect With Trucking Factoring Companies | Trucker Copilot"
  description="One request reaches participating transportation factoring and specialty finance companies. Compare programs and keep every funded load connected in the app."
>
  <section class="hero" style="padding-bottom:2.5rem;">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Funding Network</span>
      <h1>The right capital starts with the right connection.</h1>
      <p class="lead" style="color:var(--text-muted); max-width:44em;">
        Trucker Copilot connects carriers with participating specialty finance companies that
        understand the transportation industry. The network gives carriers a clearer path to
        evaluate providers while keeping load activity, documents, and funding communication
        connected.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:1rem;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section__intro">
        <h2>Why a network matters</h2>
        <p>
          Not every carrier has the same freight, customers, volume, history, or operating needs.
          One finance company may be a strong fit for an owner operator while another is better
          equipped for a growing fleet, a specialized freight segment, or a larger credit facility.
          Trucker Copilot creates access without pretending every provider or program is the same.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="mt-2">What carriers can evaluate</h2>
      <div class="grid grid--2 mt-2">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card__icon">🚚</div>
          <h3>Industry experience</h3>
          <p>Look for a provider that understands freight documentation, broker and shipper payment behavior, and the cash demands of operating trucks.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card__icon">📋</div>
          <h3>Funding structure</h3>
          <p>Review recourse, nonrecourse, advance, reserve, fee, term, and minimum requirements directly with the provider.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card__icon">🛎️</div>
          <h3>Service and visibility</h3>
          <p>Understand how questions, exceptions, collections, and funding status are handled after the agreement is signed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card__icon">🔗</div>
          <h3>Technology connection</h3>
          <p>Choose a provider that can receive the transaction through Trucker Copilot and operate through the FactorEvo infrastructure.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section__intro">
        <h2>How the connection works</h2>
        <p>
          Tell us about your operation. Trucker Copilot can route your request to participating
          providers aligned with the information you submit. Providers make their own credit,
          eligibility, pricing, and funding decisions. You review the available terms and choose
          whether to proceed.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="disclaimer mt-2">
        <strong>Important:</strong> Trucker Copilot is not a lender or factoring company and does
        not guarantee that a provider will approve or fund a transaction. All financing arrangements
        are directly between the carrier and the selected finance company.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBand
    headline="Find capital that understands trucking."
    primaryLabel="Connect Me With a Finance Company"
    primaryHref="/download"
    secondaryLabel="Already Have a Provider? Sign In"
    secondaryHref="/download"
  />
</Base>
